    <title>Slope-Intercept Form of a Line</title>
    <p><em>Slope-Intercept Form of a Line</em> relates the standard <m>y = mx + b</m> form of a 
        line with arithmetic sequences (<em>Linear Growth, Recursion and Slope</em>). Examples of 
        graphing a line from the equation and of finding the equation, given the graph are presented.</p>
        
